\mathbb{R}_{+}^{n}=\{x=(x_{1},\cdots,x_{n})\in\mathbb{R}^{n}\mid x_{n}>0  \}
K(x,y)=\frac{2x_{n}}{n\alpha(n)}\frac{1}{\lvert x-y\rvert^{n}}
x\in \mathbb{R}^{n}_{+},y\in\partial\mathbb{R}^{n}_{+}
B(0,1)
K(x,y)=\frac{1-\lvert x \rvert^{2}}{n\alpha(n)}\frac{1}{\lvert x-y\rvert^{n}}
x\in B(0,1) ,y\in\partial B(0,1)
\int_{\partial U} K(x,y) \:\mathrm{d}y =1
\partial U
